ABUJA – An expert in the real sector of Nigeria, Uche Egwuagu has advised government at all levels to do away with bureaucracies associated with land acquisition, insisting that only through such means will the country bridge its mass housing deficits. The realtor who specialises in low cost housing scheme for middle income earners, noted that government should not shy away from partnering private developers, especially when they boast of good credibility. He gave the advise, while unveiling its latest housing projects design. ICPC Chairman Warns Developer Against Shoddy Execution Of… ‘Land Surveyors Play Very Critical Role In The Construction… ” As an expert in the real sector of the Nigerian economy, I would say government can help real estate firms by removing bureaucracies involved in land accusations to help firms like ours continue to provide low-cost houses for Nigerians. “I delved into real estate investment through my uncle who is a surveyor, we used to work on layouts and acres of community lands and it helped me know more about the intricacies of land development, through that I horned my interest in real estate. “I officially started my estate firm in 2017 and since then on unique selling point, has been the focus on ensuring that an average Nigerian has a decent accommodation without paying a fortune. “We have no business competing with the big names in the real sector, all we try to do is provide the best houses at an affordable cost,” the realtor stressed.